  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Virtual Cash Terminals (VCTs) track cash flow and card payments/refunds on tickets, helping ensure accurate register balancing at the end of the day. VCTs are now optional to accommodate varied business needs, allowing transactions to be recorded outside our software. Two new settings enable users to customize the ticket closure process without requiring a VCT or payment, ensuring that inventory is still managed effectively within RepairQ.</p><p>If you open a VCT, we recommend closing it daily for cash reconciliation. This process, handled by Shift Leads or Managers, should be performed on each computer or device paired to a VCT. Closing your VCT daily helps reconcile cash counts and audit for payment discrepancies.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: VCTs and cash reconciliation do not contribute to sales or COGS reporting, as this information is pulled directly from ticket data. They should not be used to calculate sales projections.</p><h3 id=\"AssignaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)toAcceptPayments-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2717089793\" rel=\"nofollow\">Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2348187679\" rel=\"nofollow\">Virtual Cash Terminal: Ticket Payment Settings</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933901843/Virtual+Cash+Terminal+VCT+Setup\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933901843\" data-linked-resource-version=\"16\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Setting up a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT)</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803641/Virtual+Cash+Terminal+VCT+Cash+Transfers\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803641\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) Cash Transfers</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933541484/Configuring+a+Cash+Drawer+to+Open+Automatically+When+a+Receipt+is+Printed\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933541484\" data-linked-resource-version=\"3\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Configure a Cash Drawer to Open Automatically When a Receipt is Printed</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"createlink\" href=\"/wiki/pages/createpage.action?spaceKey=SCD&amp;title=Closing%20a%20Virtual%20Cash%20Terminal%20%28VCT%29&amp;linkCreation=true&amp;fromPageId=1933639827\">Closing a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT)</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934229524/Reports+Cash+Reconciliation\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934229524\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Cash Reconciliation</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"AssignaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)toAcceptPayments-AcceptPaymentswithaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)\">Accept Payments with a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT)</h2><h3 id=\"AssignaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)toAcceptPayments-AssignaVCTtoaComputer\">Assign a VCT to a Computer</h3><p>On the right side of the Navigation Bar, click the <strong>Location Short Name</strong> drop-down to expand a list of options, then click <strong>Assign a VCT</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Assign VCT 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Assign%20VCT%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Terminal Management page, find the VCT you would like to assign to your computer. Under the Actions column, click the <strong>Start/Assign</strong> button to begin assigning your VCT.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Terminal Assignment page, select the payment methods you want to receive on this VCT. If you leave a payment method unchecked, you cannot add a transaction with this type of payment method until you reassign the VCT with that method.</p><p><strong>Note:\u00a0</strong>New payment methods are managed by going to <strong>Location Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Payments</strong> \u2192 <strong>Payment Methods</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>If you have selected <strong>Accept Cash</strong>, enter in the Starting Cash amount in your cash drawer. This amount should match the float assigned to the VCT, ensuring that the terminal begins with the correct balance.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>If you have selected <strong>Accept Credit Card</strong> and have set up an <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157/Integrated+Payment+Processing+-+Start+Here\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295157\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">integrated payment processor</a>, select the Payment Device that will pair with this VCT.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"380\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Once you have made your selections, click Start to assign your VCT. You can now add transactions to tickets and RepairQ will track all payments made on this cash terminal. The Terminal Management page will show additional information including the current status of the VCT, which staff member started the VCT, and which staff member last updated the VCT. You can also view payment method assignments, pause/de-assign the VCT, or close/cash out the VCT.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%206.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%207.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"AssignaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)toAcceptPayments-CashFloatDiscrepancies\">Cash Float Discrepancies</h3><p>If the starting cash amount entered for the VCT does not match the assigned float, a notification will appear on the Terminal Management screen to alert you of the discrepancy.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"VCT Float Warning.png\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/VCT%20Float%20Warning.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><hr/><h2 id=\"AssignaVirtualCashTerminal(VCT)toAcceptPayments-Pause/De-AssignaVCT\">Pause/De-Assign a VCT</h2><p>RepairQ allows users to pause and reassign a VCT if they need to temporarily pause VCT access or assign the VCT to a new computer. If the VCT was paused after accepting cash transactions, the user must enter the <strong>beginning cash balance\u00a0</strong>when re-assigning the VCT instead of the current balance in the cash drawer.</p><p /><p>Navigate to the Terminal Management page and click the Pause/De-Assign button under Actions. The VCT will update to Suspended status. Click the <strong>Start/Assign</strong> button to begin the VCT assignment process.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%208.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933639827/Payments%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p><p />",
